		"Id": "chassisdef_diomede_D-M3D-QM",
		"Name": "Diomede",
		"Details": "Intended for use in more organized and somewhat well-supplied pirate bands, the D-M3D-QM Quartermaster or Q.M. for short is a deep modification for Diomede IndustrialMech. It retains Diomede signature hoists and saw for hauling and mauling, and its Heavy Plate armor and CASE-II-ish makes it almost impossible to quickly disable. As its nickname suggests, Q.Ms are often used by pirates second in command and armed with a small, but versatile arsenal allowing it to act both as an anchor for its band and handle possible “misunderstandings” when it comes to loot. Due to the nature of pirate-warband produced weaponry, its cooling system can barely cope with heat.  It does have a glimmer of hope, however,  in the fitment of the Pirate Acceleration Myomer. Pirate Acceleration Myomer (aka PAM) is a new technology developed in the Oberon Confederation by Grimm Manufacturing, this Diomede can get up to speed in short bursts thanks to its inclusion.\n\n <b><color=#e51717>Pafftek Industries Sub-mod</color></b>\n\n <b><color=#5F24AC>Designed by: Combin</color></b>",
		"Icon": "uixTxrIcon_diomede"
	},
